1
00:02:46,320 --> 00:02:48,280
This is my father's study.

2
00:02:49,040 --> 00:02:50,280
And now,

3
00:02:51,440 --> 00:02:53,440
Grandma has allowed me to use this room.

4
00:02:59,080 --> 00:02:59,920
Do you see anything?

5
00:03:00,960 --> 00:03:02,440
Oh…

6
00:03:06,920 --> 00:03:09,320
I feel strangely familiar with this room.

7
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:47,520
What did you see?

8
00:03:50,760 --> 00:03:53,840
This room used to be a nursery.

9
00:03:54,440 --> 00:03:57,440
As far as I can remember,
my father used to sit right here.

10
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:02,200
Or did you see something more,
some kind of vision from the past?

11
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:04,040
No.

12
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:05,480
This time it feels like

13
00:04:05,560 --> 00:04:08,240
I have to touch something first

14
00:04:08,320 --> 00:04:10,080
before I can connect to it.

15
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:13,400
So let me try again.

16
00:04:23,560 --> 00:04:25,080
Do you see anything, Kluay?

17
00:04:26,560 --> 00:04:27,760
I don't see anything.

18
00:04:28,400 --> 00:04:30,320
Maybe my mind isn't steady enough.

19
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:34,880
Let me try one more time.

20
00:04:39,080 --> 00:04:40,240
Or…

21
00:04:40,960 --> 00:04:43,760
did you see anything at all
that might help describe

22
00:04:43,840 --> 00:04:45,640
what it was like?

23
00:04:45,720 --> 00:04:48,440
In case I remember something
that can help you.

24
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:52,440
Well, what I saw was

25
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:55,360
piles of children's toys.

26
00:04:55,440 --> 00:04:58,120
Small cots.

27
00:04:58,640 --> 00:05:03,360
And a mobile with animal shapes.

28
00:05:04,280 --> 00:05:06,200
And…

29
00:05:14,880 --> 00:05:15,720
What is it, Kluay?

30
00:05:28,840 --> 00:05:29,920
Children's toys?

31
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:33,080
That's what I saw hanging in this room.

32
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:36,280
You said you heard children's voices.

33
00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:39,120
How many children?

34
00:05:40,520 --> 00:05:41,520
Um…

35
00:05:42,840 --> 00:05:47,360
I saw children's toys.

36
00:05:47,440 --> 00:05:51,400
There was a wardrobe and baby cots.

37
00:05:53,160 --> 00:05:54,680
There were two baby cots.

38
00:05:55,280 --> 00:05:57,320
So there were two children in this room.

39
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:49,120
No, Sin.

40
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:51,720
Ouch.

41
00:06:53,080 --> 00:06:55,520
Aunt Nong. Aunt Nong, are you okay?

42
00:06:56,360 --> 00:06:59,000
You know it's hot, and you were
still going to do that to him?

43
00:06:59,080 --> 00:07:00,800
That cripple doesn't know anything.

44
00:07:01,400 --> 00:07:04,800
His leg has no feeling.
Why should you even care about him?

45
00:07:04,880 --> 00:07:06,040
He may not feel it,

46
00:07:06,120 --> 00:07:08,640
but his skin could blister
if it's hot water.

47
00:07:09,240 --> 00:07:11,920
Sin, why are you so cruel?

48
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:14,320
Then why is he so obsessed with Warat?

49
00:07:15,440 --> 00:07:17,200
If they love each other that much,

50
00:07:17,280 --> 00:07:20,200
one day I'll tie them together

51
00:07:20,280 --> 00:07:21,520
and let them die together.

52
00:07:25,320 --> 00:07:26,800
You're back, Jirasin?

53
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:33,520
Why do you ask?

54
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:35,760
I don't care about you.

55
00:07:37,560 --> 00:07:39,120
I just want to ask,

56
00:07:40,080 --> 00:07:41,480
you met Warat, didn't you?

57
00:07:41,560 --> 00:07:44,520
How was he? Is he doing well?

58
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:46,520
Did he ask about me?

59
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:48,640
Will he come here again?

60
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:50,040
Are you still asleep, Uncle?

61
00:07:50,120 --> 00:07:51,640
That's why you're rambling nonsense.

62
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:53,960
Wake up already.

63
00:07:54,760 --> 00:07:56,920
And remember this. No child

64
00:07:57,000 --> 00:08:00,160
can ever make peace
with someone who killed their father.

65
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:02,560
What are you talking about?

66
00:08:02,640 --> 00:08:05,120
Wow, you still don't realize it,
Uncle Rut?

67
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:07,520
You're the one
who caused Warat's father to die.

68
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:08,560
Sin!

69
00:08:09,080 --> 00:08:11,920
I know you secretly went
to visit Mr. Wichan.

70
00:08:13,080 --> 00:08:14,720
And three days later,

71
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:17,560
he died.
If it wasn't you, then who did it?

72
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:18,880
I didn't do anything.

73
00:08:18,960 --> 00:08:19,880
I went to visit Wichan.

74
00:08:20,680 --> 00:08:22,160
You can fool everyone else.

75
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:26,560
You can even fool yourself.
But you can't fool Warat.

76
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:28,160
Stop dreaming foolish dreams

77
00:08:28,240 --> 00:08:30,600
that he'll ever be good to you.

78
00:08:30,680 --> 00:08:34,799
And if you don't stop,
I'll be the one to tell him myself

79
00:08:34,880 --> 00:08:36,039
that you killed his father.

80
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:37,039
Sin!

81
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:39,120
Sin, come back here right now! Sin!

82
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:40,240
Sin, come back here!

83
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:41,880
- Sin!
- Mr. Rut.

84
00:08:41,960 --> 00:08:43,440
- Sin!
- Mr. Rut.

85
00:08:43,520 --> 00:08:45,760
Go after him. I'll slap his mouth shut!

86
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:47,880
Sin, you ungrateful bastard!

87
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:49,600
Come back here, Sin!

88
00:08:50,240 --> 00:08:51,320
Look at him.

89
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:55,280
Calm down.

90
00:08:58,400 --> 00:09:01,160
But is what Sin said true?

91
00:09:01,920 --> 00:09:03,880
Why didn't I know anything about this?

92
00:09:04,400 --> 00:09:06,720
When did you go see Mr. Wichan?

93
00:09:07,720 --> 00:09:09,360
I'm Wichan's friend.

94
00:09:10,160 --> 00:09:11,480
I can visit him whenever I want.

95
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:30,320
If you really didn't do
anything to Mr. Wichan,

96
00:09:30,880 --> 00:09:32,680
then why are you afraid?

97
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:38,360
And besides,
Mr. Warat seems like a reasonable person.

98
00:09:38,440 --> 00:09:40,640
He wouldn't just believe Sin so easily.

99
00:09:41,240 --> 00:09:42,320
Tomorrow

100
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:44,200
I'm going to see Warat at Vanich Mall.

101
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:48,360
If Sin keeps getting in the way like this,

102
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:49,880
maybe

103
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:53,280
I'll have to tell Warat the whole truth.

104
00:09:56,680 --> 00:09:58,680
Please calm down.

105
00:09:58,760 --> 00:10:01,000
Right now you're angry at Sin.

106
00:10:01,640 --> 00:10:02,920
And Sin himself

107
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:05,160
is trying to adjust to Mr. Warat.

108
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:09,360
Once things settle,
everything will be better.

109
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:15,960
You've waited this long already.
What's a little longer?

110
00:10:16,040 --> 00:10:17,240
No.

111
00:10:17,840 --> 00:10:19,280
It's time

112
00:10:20,360 --> 00:10:22,520
for Warat to know the truth.

113
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:29,800
If those children really are
Ms. Mysterious's children,

114
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:33,800
then that means Ms. Mysterious
and my dad had two children together.

115
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:40,280
And your dad had to be separated
from Ms. Mysterious and the children.

116
00:10:40,360 --> 00:10:42,440
It might have made him miss them deeply,

117
00:10:42,520 --> 00:10:45,240
so deeply that he turned
this room into his office.

118
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:47,360
Have you ever thought that

119
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:49,920
one of those two children

120
00:10:50,520 --> 00:10:51,760
might be me?

121
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:54,400
Um…

122
00:10:54,480 --> 00:10:56,840
You're right. I forgot about that.

123
00:10:57,560 --> 00:10:58,600
Or maybe you didn't think of it

124
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:00,960
because you knew it was impossible.

125
00:11:01,880 --> 00:11:02,840
Oh, Mr. Warat.

126
00:11:18,640 --> 00:11:20,000
Hello.

127
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:24,520
Is she here?

128
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:26,400
Yes.

129
00:11:28,920 --> 00:11:31,840
Ask her who my real parents are.

130
00:11:31,920 --> 00:11:33,600
Who is Ms. Mysterious to me?

131
00:11:33,680 --> 00:11:35,760
Ask her. Go ahead.

132
00:11:36,760 --> 00:11:40,040
If I could communicate with her,
we would've known all of this long ago.

133
00:11:41,640 --> 00:11:42,840
Let go.

134
00:11:43,480 --> 00:11:44,520
Right?

135
00:11:48,120 --> 00:11:50,640
But at least the fact that she appeared

136
00:11:50,720 --> 00:11:55,920
means that the information I found
might actually be true, right?

137
00:12:02,400 --> 00:12:03,480
What did she say?

138
00:12:04,080 --> 00:12:07,040
She… she didn't answer at all.

139
00:12:07,840 --> 00:12:12,200
Every time she appears
or tries to communicate with me,

140
00:12:12,280 --> 00:12:14,320
she never moves her lips.

141
00:12:16,560 --> 00:12:19,200
But Ms. Mysterious,

142
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:22,880
today you look very faint.

143
00:12:26,760 --> 00:12:27,800
Mr. Warat,

144
00:12:27,880 --> 00:12:30,640
I think we should let
Ms. Mysterious go for now.

145
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:32,800
She looks very weak.

146
00:12:33,320 --> 00:12:35,240
And what if she doesn't come back again?

147
00:12:36,440 --> 00:12:38,280
I believe she will come back.

148
00:12:39,520 --> 00:12:42,400
Please. I feel sorry for her.

149
00:12:45,840 --> 00:12:46,840
Alright.

150
00:13:05,520 --> 00:13:09,160
I understand now
why Ms. Mysterious is losing strength.

151
00:13:09,840 --> 00:13:10,720
Ow.

152
00:13:11,960 --> 00:13:13,200
Grandma.

153
00:13:13,280 --> 00:13:14,680
What were you doing in that room?

154
00:13:17,680 --> 00:13:20,000
Babe and I went in,

155
00:13:20,080 --> 00:13:22,920
uh, to talk about some unfinished work.

156
00:13:23,680 --> 00:13:24,520
Yes.

157
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:27,240
Warat was worried he wouldn't
be able to go to the office,

158
00:13:27,320 --> 00:13:30,480
so he wanted to leave the work
with me to handle instead.

159
00:13:31,920 --> 00:13:32,960
No more questions, right?

160
00:13:34,120 --> 00:13:35,000
I'm going to bed.

161
00:13:35,080 --> 00:13:36,160
Normally,

162
00:13:36,680 --> 00:13:40,040
I don't let people go in
and out of that room very often.

163
00:13:40,560 --> 00:13:42,160
But since it's you, Warat,

164
00:13:42,240 --> 00:13:44,160
I allowed it to be used as your office.

165
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:47,920
I just didn't expect anyone else
to go in and use it as well.

166
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:50,600
Grandma, Kluay is…

167
00:13:50,680 --> 00:13:53,120
You don't need to keep repeating
what the two of you are.

168
00:13:54,160 --> 00:13:55,640
I myself

169
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:58,160
still need time to adjust.

170
00:13:59,400 --> 00:14:02,400
Let's take it step by step.

171
00:14:03,120 --> 00:14:06,080
That room contains many
of your father's personal belongings.

172
00:14:06,680 --> 00:14:08,600
Think carefully before you do anything.

173
00:14:11,680 --> 00:14:14,400
You've been staring at me
for quite a while.

174
00:14:16,120 --> 00:14:17,200
Oh.

175
00:14:17,720 --> 00:14:20,920
I have something I want to ask you,
Madam Chairwoman.

176
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:23,120
You can call me Grandma, like Rat does.

177
00:14:25,280 --> 00:14:26,120
Thank you.

178
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:30,360
I wanted to ask,
aside from praying in the prayer room,

179
00:14:30,440 --> 00:14:33,680
do you worship
anything else in particular?

180
00:14:33,760 --> 00:14:36,640
Like household spirits,

181
00:14:36,720 --> 00:14:38,040
guardian deities, or anything like that?

182
00:14:38,120 --> 00:14:41,000
You still haven't stopped
obsessing over things like this?

183
00:14:43,280 --> 00:14:44,840
It's not like that.

184
00:14:44,920 --> 00:14:47,240
I just wanted to ask just in case.

185
00:14:47,320 --> 00:14:49,200
Let me warn you first.

186
00:14:49,720 --> 00:14:53,280
Do not even think about performing
any white magic or black magic here.

187
00:14:54,040 --> 00:14:55,560
If you do, I will deal with you.

188
00:14:56,440 --> 00:14:57,760
Because this place

189
00:14:57,840 --> 00:15:00,040
contains only sacred
and auspicious things.

190
00:15:00,120 --> 00:15:01,240
Remember that.

191
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:03,360
- Yes.
- Rat.

192
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:05,880
Take good care of your girlfriend.

193
00:15:06,480 --> 00:15:07,320
Yes.

194
00:15:23,600 --> 00:15:25,000
Why didn't you talk to me first?

195
00:15:25,080 --> 00:15:27,720
I just wanted to find a way

196
00:15:27,800 --> 00:15:29,600
to see Ms. Mysterious as soon as possible.

197
00:15:29,680 --> 00:15:31,880
But she isn't an ordinary person.

198
00:15:32,760 --> 00:15:34,240
She's Mrs. Wanee Vanich.

199
00:15:43,920 --> 00:15:45,320
Ugh.

200
00:15:46,560 --> 00:15:48,080
Another day's gone.

201
00:15:53,040 --> 00:15:55,480
I will find a way
to help you as soon as possible.

202
00:16:06,160 --> 00:16:07,520
<i>Det asked me to give you this.</i>

203
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:08,800
I don't want to read it.

204
00:16:08,880 --> 00:16:09,920
Hey, why not?

205
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:11,680
I already took it.

206
00:16:24,880 --> 00:16:27,440
Oh, Mr. Warat, can you listen to me first?

207
00:16:27,520 --> 00:16:28,720
Don't complain yet.

208
00:16:28,800 --> 00:16:31,640
I told you I just came
to run a quick errand.

209
00:16:31,720 --> 00:16:33,360
I'll be right back.

210
00:16:43,640 --> 00:16:45,800
<i>I'm asking you for one last favor.</i>

211
00:16:45,880 --> 00:16:49,280
<i>After meeting you,</i>
<i>I'll have to fly to the US immediately.</i>

212
00:16:49,360 --> 00:16:51,080
<i>There's no plan to return to Thailand yet.</i>

213
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:53,760
<i>Please come meet me one last time</i>

214
00:16:53,840 --> 00:16:56,000
<i>if you still value our friendship.</i>

215
00:16:56,080 --> 00:16:57,080
<i>Det.</i>

216
00:17:12,680 --> 00:17:13,760
Det.

217
00:17:14,280 --> 00:17:15,440
What are you doing?

218
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:22,640
Thank you, Det, for respecting me.

219
00:17:24,760 --> 00:17:26,440
I've thought about it,

220
00:17:26,520 --> 00:17:28,040
and I really did go too far.

221
00:17:28,760 --> 00:17:29,800
How about this?

222
00:17:29,880 --> 00:17:33,920
I'll call Kluay and tell her
that the letter was fake.

223
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:34,960
Is that okay?

224
00:17:37,160 --> 00:17:38,280
No need.

225
00:17:38,360 --> 00:17:40,960
If she goes and doesn't meet anyone,
she'll go back on her own.

226
00:17:41,040 --> 00:17:42,240
Oh.

227
00:17:42,320 --> 00:17:45,520
Aren't you afraid Kluay will be angry?

228
00:17:45,600 --> 00:17:47,600
Going there
and not seeing anyone like that?

229
00:17:51,480 --> 00:17:53,120
Det…

230
00:17:54,120 --> 00:17:55,680
I'm sorry.

231
00:17:56,400 --> 00:17:57,920
I'm really sorry.

232
00:17:58,440 --> 00:17:59,440
Let's make up, okay?

233
00:18:00,360 --> 00:18:01,880
Please.

234
00:18:02,400 --> 00:18:03,280
Hm?

235
00:18:03,800 --> 00:18:05,080
Okay.

236
00:18:05,160 --> 00:18:06,160
Hey.

237
00:18:09,320 --> 00:18:10,600
Smile a little.

238
00:18:13,720 --> 00:18:14,720
Well,

239
00:18:16,120 --> 00:18:17,560
that matter is over now.

240
00:18:18,760 --> 00:18:19,800
From now on,

241
00:18:20,640 --> 00:18:22,120
there won't be any more trouble.

242
00:18:22,720 --> 00:18:23,760
I'm so happy.

243
00:18:24,280 --> 00:18:25,880
You've forgiven me.

244
00:18:25,960 --> 00:18:29,280
If that's the case, how about we go eat,

245
00:18:29,360 --> 00:18:30,640
then watch a movie?

246
00:18:30,720 --> 00:18:33,920
Or if you want to go shopping,
that's fine too.

247
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:35,360
How does that sound?

248
00:18:35,440 --> 00:18:37,000
No. I still have a lot of work.

249
00:18:38,480 --> 00:18:40,640
So you're still mad at me?

250
00:18:45,520 --> 00:18:46,360
Alright, I'll go.

251
00:18:47,440 --> 00:18:48,960
You're the cutest.

252
00:18:49,040 --> 00:18:51,480
Then I'll go change clothes for a moment.

253
00:19:18,760 --> 00:19:20,080
This one.

254
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:22,040
Let's go.

255
00:19:23,680 --> 00:19:24,880
You shameless bitch!

256
00:19:24,960 --> 00:19:25,800
Ouch!

257
00:19:25,880 --> 00:19:27,880
Hey, wait.

258
00:19:27,960 --> 00:19:30,440
We've never met before.
Why did you slap me?

259
00:19:30,520 --> 00:19:32,120
You're meeting with someone's man here

260
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:33,520
and you're still asking?

261
00:19:33,600 --> 00:19:35,280
Uh… someone's man?

262
00:19:43,200 --> 00:19:44,280
Hey.

263
00:19:44,360 --> 00:19:46,720
Just looking at the photo,
you can tell it's not me.

264
00:19:46,800 --> 00:19:48,960
How could it not be? That's clearly you.

265
00:19:49,040 --> 00:19:51,680
Well, the face does look similar,

266
00:19:51,760 --> 00:19:52,920
but…

267
00:19:55,040 --> 00:19:56,200
That's not me, right?

268
00:19:56,800 --> 00:19:58,360
Mistresses are all like this.

269
00:19:58,440 --> 00:19:59,520
Don't talk so much.

270
00:20:00,120 --> 00:20:00,960
Or do you wanna die?

271
00:20:01,040 --> 00:20:02,440
Hey.

272
00:20:02,520 --> 00:20:03,720
That's not enough.

273
00:20:04,280 --> 00:20:05,120
Where are you…?

274
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:06,280
Where are you going?

275
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:08,680
Please, calm down.

276
00:20:09,960 --> 00:20:11,000
Hey!

277
00:20:14,280 --> 00:20:15,640
Don't go after her.

278
00:20:18,880 --> 00:20:20,840
- Uh, sorry…
- Oops.

279
00:20:23,240 --> 00:20:25,440
We meet again, Kluay.

280
00:20:25,520 --> 00:20:26,640
Kluay.

281
00:20:28,800 --> 00:20:31,280
Why do you look like this, my friend?

282
00:20:31,360 --> 00:20:33,520
You're soaked
like a puppy that fell into the water.

283
00:20:34,680 --> 00:20:35,520
Wow.

284
00:20:35,600 --> 00:20:38,560
Karma really sticks fast.

285
00:20:38,640 --> 00:20:40,400
Look at you,

286
00:20:40,480 --> 00:20:43,760
soaked exactly like
what you did to me the other day.

287
00:20:44,920 --> 00:20:46,560
Did it really have to go this far?

288
00:20:47,960 --> 00:20:49,640
Kluay, I'm sorry.

289
00:20:55,800 --> 00:20:56,640
- Let go.
- Ameena.

290
00:20:58,920 --> 00:21:00,440
This time, I'll let it go.

291
00:21:01,280 --> 00:21:02,400
But please, Det,

292
00:21:02,920 --> 00:21:04,400
stay away from me
for the rest of your life.

293
00:21:07,120 --> 00:21:08,760
I never had a friend like you.

294
00:21:10,680 --> 00:21:11,680
Kluay.

295
00:21:33,360 --> 00:21:34,960
- Ouch, oh my!
- Oh!

296
00:21:35,880 --> 00:21:36,960
- Som.
- Arnon.

297
00:21:37,040 --> 00:21:38,360
I was about to go look for you.

298
00:21:38,440 --> 00:21:39,680
I was coming to see you too.

299
00:21:39,760 --> 00:21:42,240
- So, have you seen this yet?
- Have you seen it?

300
00:21:46,920 --> 00:21:48,480
Rat.

301
00:21:49,320 --> 00:21:50,360
Your girlfriend

302
00:21:50,440 --> 00:21:52,720
hasn't even been in this house
for a full week

303
00:21:52,800 --> 00:21:54,440
and something already happens.

304
00:21:54,520 --> 00:21:57,200
So what are you supposed to do next?

305
00:21:58,520 --> 00:21:59,920
Grandma, please calm down.

306
00:22:00,640 --> 00:22:02,400
Let's wait for her
to come back and explain.

307
00:22:02,920 --> 00:22:05,600
I'm sure something about this isn't right.

308
00:22:06,520 --> 00:22:07,960
There's no reason

309
00:22:08,040 --> 00:22:09,800
for Kluay to be someone's mistress.

310
00:22:09,880 --> 00:22:11,560
If what you're saying is that

311
00:22:11,640 --> 00:22:14,520
Kluay was framed and physically assaulted,

312
00:22:14,600 --> 00:22:15,880
that's even worse.

313
00:22:15,960 --> 00:22:19,960
That means
this woman has a lot of enemies.

314
00:22:20,040 --> 00:22:23,280
And that means
you shouldn't continue with her.

315
00:22:23,360 --> 00:22:24,200
No.

316
00:22:25,080 --> 00:22:27,800
She's the only woman I'm going to be with.

317
00:22:27,880 --> 00:22:28,880
She's good enough for me.

318
00:22:30,760 --> 00:22:32,960
There she is. Perfect timing.

319
00:22:33,760 --> 00:22:35,120
Are you going to say it

320
00:22:35,200 --> 00:22:39,760
or do I need to interrogate you
about what happened to you,

321
00:22:39,840 --> 00:22:40,960
Boonsita?

322
00:22:45,440 --> 00:22:47,200
I told you I don't know anything.

323
00:22:47,720 --> 00:22:49,080
Why won't you believe me?

324
00:22:49,160 --> 00:22:51,240
No one is stupid enough to believe you.

325
00:22:51,320 --> 00:22:53,960
People put up with you
because they're tired of you.

326
00:22:54,040 --> 00:22:55,120
Try reflecting on yourself for once.

327
00:22:55,200 --> 00:22:56,640
Stop insulting me right now.

328
00:22:56,720 --> 00:22:59,880
I will stop because I'm not
coming back here ever again.

329
00:22:59,960 --> 00:23:02,000
If you want me to behave myself,

330
00:23:02,840 --> 00:23:04,600
then just stay here

331
00:23:05,640 --> 00:23:07,560
and cut ties with Kluay.

332
00:23:08,160 --> 00:23:09,640
That ends everything, Det.

333
00:23:10,360 --> 00:23:11,280
Ends it?

334
00:23:11,800 --> 00:23:13,920
As long as you keep suspecting her and me,

335
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:15,400
this will keep going in circles.

336
00:23:15,480 --> 00:23:17,280
You say I'm suspecting you,

337
00:23:17,800 --> 00:23:20,240
but you only ever defend yourself.

338
00:23:20,320 --> 00:23:22,080
If you hadn't written that letter to her,

339
00:23:22,640 --> 00:23:23,520
would this have happened?

340
00:23:24,040 --> 00:23:25,880
Would it?

341
00:23:26,520 --> 00:23:27,600
Where are you going?

342
00:23:27,680 --> 00:23:29,440
I'm leaving.

343
00:23:29,520 --> 00:23:31,440
And don't threaten me with work,
with my dad,

344
00:23:31,520 --> 00:23:32,480
or with money.

345
00:23:32,560 --> 00:23:34,560
I'm not letting you go anywhere.

346
00:23:34,640 --> 00:23:36,720
- It's over, Ameena.
- Det!

347
00:23:37,640 --> 00:23:39,320
I told you not to go.

348
00:23:39,400 --> 00:23:40,960
I'm not letting you go.

349
00:23:41,040 --> 00:23:42,000
Det.

350
00:23:56,240 --> 00:23:59,000
I've been calling and messaging,
but I can't reach Kluay. What now?

351
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:03,120
The one who leaked the clip of Kluay being
slapped and accused of being a mistress,

352
00:24:03,640 --> 00:24:06,360
I'll make sure they learn their lesson.
This is a criminal case.

353
00:24:06,440 --> 00:24:07,760
But Arnon, you know, right,

354
00:24:07,840 --> 00:24:10,960
that right now Kluay is staying
at the Vanich house as Warat's girlfriend.

355
00:24:11,040 --> 00:24:13,120
If the Chairwoman sees this clip…

356
00:24:13,200 --> 00:24:16,160
this will destroy
both Kluay and Mr. Warat.

357
00:24:17,280 --> 00:24:20,440
Then we need to get that clip taken down
as fast as possible.

358
00:24:20,520 --> 00:24:21,760
Right.

359
00:24:21,840 --> 00:24:25,080
I have contacts at the unit that handles
fake news for our mall quite often.

360
00:24:25,160 --> 00:24:26,600
Call them. What are you waiting for?

361
00:24:26,680 --> 00:24:27,640
Yes.

362
00:24:33,320 --> 00:24:35,840
If you say you never knew
each other before,

363
00:24:35,920 --> 00:24:37,600
and she assaulted you,

364
00:24:37,680 --> 00:24:39,360
why didn't you file a police report?

365
00:24:39,960 --> 00:24:43,280
I'm afraid it would damage Vanich.

366
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:48,920
With the utmost respect, ma'am,

367
00:24:49,440 --> 00:24:51,360
there are comments saying that Ms. Kluay

368
00:24:51,440 --> 00:24:54,160
is the future daughter-in-law of Vanich.

369
00:24:54,760 --> 00:24:56,600
Satisfied now?

370
00:24:56,680 --> 00:24:58,920
Grandma. Please stop.

371
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:01,360
Let Kluay go shower and clean up first.

372
00:25:01,440 --> 00:25:04,280
Interrogating her now won't help anything.

373
00:25:04,360 --> 00:25:06,840
Besides, Arnon
is already handling the legal side.

374
00:25:08,200 --> 00:25:09,400
Please, stop.

375
00:25:10,480 --> 00:25:11,520
Kluay.

376
00:25:12,800 --> 00:25:13,800
Let's go.

377
00:25:34,320 --> 00:25:36,080
With the utmost respect, ma'am,

378
00:25:37,480 --> 00:25:38,920
this is footage from the CCTV.

379
00:25:41,520 --> 00:25:43,080
Ameena?

380
00:25:45,200 --> 00:25:47,560
What was she doing there?

381
00:25:49,120 --> 00:25:50,960
Was this Ameena's doing?

382
00:25:52,320 --> 00:25:54,520
I believe so, ma'am.

383
00:25:54,600 --> 00:25:57,600
The two of them have had bad blood
since their school days.

384
00:25:57,680 --> 00:26:00,720
Ms. Ameena has been following
and provoking Ms. Kluay ever since.

385
00:26:02,880 --> 00:26:05,760
Do not let Rat know about this
under any circumstances.

386
00:26:06,640 --> 00:26:08,400
No matter what kind of person she is,

387
00:26:08,480 --> 00:26:11,760
Ameena is more suitable for Rat.

388
00:26:12,360 --> 00:26:13,520
Yes, ma'am.

389
00:26:14,200 --> 00:26:17,160
Who says family background doesn't matter?

390
00:26:19,240 --> 00:26:20,680
No matter what,

391
00:26:20,760 --> 00:26:25,880
my Rat must have
a woman who is fully qualified

392
00:26:26,560 --> 00:26:28,000
in every way.

393
00:26:28,680 --> 00:26:30,280
Most importantly,

394
00:26:30,800 --> 00:26:34,960
I don't want history to repeat itself
like with Wichan and…

395
00:26:37,040 --> 00:26:38,400
Ma'am, be careful.

396
00:26:39,240 --> 00:26:40,080
What is this?

397
00:26:43,160 --> 00:26:46,080
BOONYAVEJ HOSPITAL

398
00:26:46,160 --> 00:26:48,080
GET WELL SOON

399
00:26:54,320 --> 00:26:56,800
The doctor said you're fine.

400
00:26:57,400 --> 00:26:58,880
Once this IV bag is finished,

401
00:26:58,960 --> 00:27:00,720
you can go home if you want.

402
00:27:03,280 --> 00:27:04,680
Det, look.

403
00:27:05,280 --> 00:27:07,360
So many people are worried about me.

404
00:27:07,440 --> 00:27:08,640
I can't even reply to all the messages.

405
00:27:08,720 --> 00:27:11,360
You shouldn't post photos
of yourself getting an IV

406
00:27:11,440 --> 00:27:12,760
on social media.

407
00:27:12,840 --> 00:27:13,880
It's private.

408
00:27:13,960 --> 00:27:15,840
This is exactly the kind of thing
you should post.

409
00:27:15,920 --> 00:27:17,480
Everyone's worried about me.

410
00:27:17,560 --> 00:27:20,080
If I don't tell them,
they'll be upset with me.

411
00:27:31,040 --> 00:27:32,040
Na…

412
00:27:32,560 --> 00:27:34,360
Well…

413
00:27:35,240 --> 00:27:36,240
Well…

414
00:27:37,040 --> 00:27:39,200
I have something I want to tell you.

415
00:27:39,280 --> 00:27:40,280
But…

416
00:27:41,000 --> 00:27:42,000
Det.

417
00:27:43,720 --> 00:27:45,560
Thank you, Det.

418
00:27:48,200 --> 00:27:51,280
You've always been good to me.

419
00:27:54,080 --> 00:27:55,120
You know,

420
00:27:55,800 --> 00:27:57,280
I was even thinking,

421
00:27:58,280 --> 00:28:01,960
if you hadn't helped me,

422
00:28:04,720 --> 00:28:06,440
by now I might've…

423
00:28:13,080 --> 00:28:14,920
Thank you so much, Det.

424
00:28:27,440 --> 00:28:29,520
So this is the future
Vanich daughter-in-law?

425
00:28:30,040 --> 00:28:33,000
I don't know how Mr. Rat
could pick her to be his girlfriend.

426
00:28:33,080 --> 00:28:34,800
Their backgrounds are worlds apart.

427
00:28:34,880 --> 00:28:37,160
There's even a scandal clip
about stealing someone else's man.

428
00:28:37,240 --> 00:28:39,160
They suit each other perfectly,
don't they?

429
00:28:39,880 --> 00:28:41,520
His mother was a mistress,

430
00:28:42,160 --> 00:28:43,680
and he deserves

431
00:28:43,760 --> 00:28:44,920
to get this kind of woman.

432
00:28:45,000 --> 00:28:46,800
Didn't you say you'd never let Kluay

433
00:28:46,880 --> 00:28:48,920
become a Vanich daughter-in-law?

434
00:28:49,000 --> 00:28:50,000
And who said

435
00:28:51,600 --> 00:28:53,600
that every woman who dates Warat

436
00:28:54,280 --> 00:28:56,160
gets to become a Vanich daughter-in-law?

437
00:28:58,360 --> 00:29:00,920
Warat will never get his hands

438
00:29:01,000 --> 00:29:03,200
on a single baht of Vanich money.

439
00:29:03,280 --> 00:29:04,720
No matter how much they love each other.

440
00:29:05,600 --> 00:29:08,120
Kluay will never live comfortably.

441
00:29:08,760 --> 00:29:10,720
I promised my sister.

442
00:29:10,800 --> 00:29:12,640
And that's exactly how it will be.

443
00:29:20,080 --> 00:29:21,240
What's wrong, Lak? Why are you crying?

444
00:29:22,800 --> 00:29:24,800
I'm scared, Sin.

445
00:29:24,880 --> 00:29:26,720
I don't want to die yet.

446
00:29:26,800 --> 00:29:29,280
What was that? How could
you die? Why would you say that?

447
00:29:29,360 --> 00:29:31,480
Did anyone do anything to you?
Tell me who did this to you?

448
00:29:32,240 --> 00:29:33,280
Kluay.

449
00:29:33,360 --> 00:29:34,560
Kluay, your friend?

450
00:29:35,160 --> 00:29:36,920
Kluay said I'm going to die.

451
00:29:37,520 --> 00:29:39,040
Lak, what did she say?

452
00:29:39,120 --> 00:29:41,240
Stop hanging out with people like that.

453
00:29:41,320 --> 00:29:43,840
But this time, Kluay was serious, Sin.

454
00:29:45,160 --> 00:29:48,120
I'm scared. I don't want to die yet.

455
00:29:50,600 --> 00:29:52,880
You won't die, Lak. There's no way.

456
00:29:53,560 --> 00:29:54,880
I don't want to die.

457
00:29:58,480 --> 00:29:59,400
You're a friend of the deceased, right?

458
00:29:59,480 --> 00:30:00,800
Sin.

459
00:30:01,640 --> 00:30:02,640
Miss.

460
00:30:02,720 --> 00:30:03,560
RESTRICTED AREA

461
00:30:03,640 --> 00:30:05,240
May I have your name, please?

462
00:30:07,640 --> 00:30:09,240
Please answer me.

463
00:30:09,320 --> 00:30:10,560
PATHUMTHANI RESCUE TEAM

464
00:30:10,640 --> 00:30:12,000
Lak.

465
00:30:12,080 --> 00:30:14,360
- Please.
- Lak.

466
00:30:14,440 --> 00:30:15,640
Please answer me.

467
00:30:16,240 --> 00:30:17,080
Lak.

468
00:30:17,160 --> 00:30:18,840
- Sin.
- Sin.

469
00:30:23,680 --> 00:30:24,760
Lak.

470
00:30:26,040 --> 00:30:26,880
Hold him back.

471
00:30:42,720 --> 00:30:45,480
- Kluay.
- Sin.

472
00:30:45,560 --> 00:30:47,600
Why is Lak like this, Kluay?

473
00:30:48,840 --> 00:30:51,520
Why is she like this?

474
00:30:53,280 --> 00:30:54,160
Sin.

475
00:30:57,920 --> 00:31:00,200
You killed my sister!
Why did you kill my sister?!

476
00:31:00,280 --> 00:31:01,760
- Why did you kill my sister?!
- Sin.

477
00:31:01,840 --> 00:31:04,080
- Officer!
- Arrest her. She killed my sister.

478
00:31:05,480 --> 00:31:07,560
Arrest her. She killed my sister.

479
00:31:08,560 --> 00:31:09,800
Arrest her.

480
00:31:11,600 --> 00:31:14,600
- She killed my sister!
- Calm down, sir. Please calm down.

481
00:31:14,680 --> 00:31:16,400
Arrest her.

482
00:31:16,480 --> 00:31:18,760
She killed my sister.
Why are you holding me back?

483
00:31:18,840 --> 00:31:20,560
<i>She killed my sister!</i>

484
00:31:23,680 --> 00:31:25,360
The law never did anything to her.

485
00:31:27,320 --> 00:31:29,440
So I had to deal with her myself.

486
00:31:29,520 --> 00:31:31,600
She looks so harmless.

487
00:31:31,680 --> 00:31:33,400
How can she be this cruel?

488
00:31:34,040 --> 00:31:36,320
She deserves worse
than what she did to Lak.

489
00:31:38,080 --> 00:31:39,080
It's almost time.

490
00:31:40,280 --> 00:31:41,800
Her time is almost up.

491
00:31:45,280 --> 00:31:46,360
Mr. Sin.

492
00:31:46,440 --> 00:31:47,280
What is it?

493
00:31:47,360 --> 00:31:49,400
You have a visitor asking to see you.

494
00:31:50,240 --> 00:31:51,560
Uncle Rut, why are you here?

495
00:31:52,080 --> 00:31:54,080
Why didn't you tell me first?

496
00:31:55,400 --> 00:31:57,280
I didn't come to see you.

497
00:31:57,880 --> 00:31:59,280
I know you're busy.

498
00:32:01,360 --> 00:32:03,000
I came to see Warat.

499
00:32:05,320 --> 00:32:07,600
But he's not here.

500
00:32:07,680 --> 00:32:09,200
He's sick.

501
00:32:13,600 --> 00:32:15,080
Are you afraid of something?

502
00:32:15,160 --> 00:32:17,680
Afraid I'll tell him the secret?

503
00:32:17,760 --> 00:32:19,160
That's why you rushed here first?

504
00:32:20,040 --> 00:32:22,600
Can't you speak nicely
to your uncle just once?

505
00:32:23,440 --> 00:32:24,640
Huh?

506
00:32:24,720 --> 00:32:26,160
But fine.

507
00:32:26,240 --> 00:32:27,880
I won't hold it against you.

508
00:32:28,480 --> 00:32:29,720
Because someone like you

509
00:32:29,800 --> 00:32:31,240
doesn't know the truth.

510
00:32:31,880 --> 00:32:33,600
I ask only one thing.

511
00:32:34,280 --> 00:32:35,360
Don't speak

512
00:32:36,040 --> 00:32:38,280
badly about Warat.

513
00:32:38,360 --> 00:32:40,440
He has nothing to do with this.

514
00:32:40,520 --> 00:32:42,520
Since Warat

515
00:32:43,040 --> 00:32:45,400
is the son of Praewilai,

516
00:32:45,920 --> 00:32:47,960
the woman who destroyed my family.

517
00:32:48,040 --> 00:32:49,360
That's the past.

518
00:32:49,880 --> 00:32:51,320
The past is the past.

519
00:32:51,400 --> 00:32:52,640
Come on.

520
00:32:52,720 --> 00:32:53,720
I understand you.

521
00:32:54,320 --> 00:32:55,720
But you need to separate things.

522
00:32:55,800 --> 00:32:57,480
All you see is benefits.

523
00:32:57,560 --> 00:32:59,200
Don't you think?

524
00:32:59,280 --> 00:33:00,520
Of course,

525
00:33:00,600 --> 00:33:02,000
I think about it.

526
00:33:02,920 --> 00:33:05,800
But I'm not obsessed
with just one thing like you.

527
00:33:05,880 --> 00:33:08,280
What I want most in life

528
00:33:08,360 --> 00:33:10,320
is the downfall of the Vanich family.

529
00:33:11,400 --> 00:33:14,200
And if I don't let you do that?

530
00:33:14,280 --> 00:33:15,920
In the past,

531
00:33:16,880 --> 00:33:19,280
your words might have scared me.

532
00:33:20,560 --> 00:33:21,800
You know

533
00:33:22,760 --> 00:33:25,120
why I came here today, right?

534
00:33:25,800 --> 00:33:27,520
What I'm going to tell Rat.

535
00:33:32,640 --> 00:33:34,280
Go on. Say it.

536
00:33:35,800 --> 00:33:37,600
I'd like to hear

537
00:33:37,680 --> 00:33:40,800
how you're going to cover up
his father's death.

538
00:33:43,120 --> 00:33:44,040
No.

539
00:33:44,800 --> 00:33:45,640
No.

540
00:33:45,720 --> 00:33:47,160
That's not it.

541
00:33:50,240 --> 00:33:51,240
Uncle.

542
00:33:51,760 --> 00:33:54,520
Uncle Rut. Uncle Rut.

543
00:33:54,600 --> 00:34:00,400
SIN

544
00:34:04,680 --> 00:34:05,960
So what?

545
00:34:06,480 --> 00:34:08,400
<i>Why don't you sound shocked at all?</i>

546
00:34:08,480 --> 00:34:10,040
<i>Or did someone already call you?</i>

547
00:34:10,120 --> 00:34:11,960
Why should I be shocked?

548
00:34:12,560 --> 00:34:15,920
Uncle Rut is always unwell.

549
00:34:17,040 --> 00:34:19,239
He goes out all the time.

550
00:34:19,320 --> 00:34:22,000
Every time he comes back,
he collapses like this.

551
00:34:22,080 --> 00:34:23,600
<i>But this isn't at home.</i>

552
00:34:23,679 --> 00:34:26,639
<i>He collapsed in the office.</i>
<i>What if it were somewhere else?</i>

553
00:34:28,080 --> 00:34:29,239
Then what?

554
00:34:30,719 --> 00:34:32,400
I'd go take care of him.

555
00:34:35,320 --> 00:34:37,159
Go back to work, Sin.

556
00:34:38,080 --> 00:34:39,960
And tell Uncle Rut

557
00:34:40,480 --> 00:34:42,320
I'll pick him up myself.

558
00:34:42,840 --> 00:34:45,520
I'm making the soup he likes.

559
00:34:46,239 --> 00:34:48,400
As soon as it's done, I'll go get him.

560
00:34:59,760 --> 00:35:02,040
You just ate it this morning.

561
00:35:03,760 --> 00:35:05,520
You want it again already?

562
00:35:14,960 --> 00:35:16,520
If I'd known it would be
this uncomfortable

563
00:35:16,600 --> 00:35:17,760
and itchy,

564
00:35:18,320 --> 00:35:19,720
I would've found another way.

565
00:35:20,840 --> 00:35:23,120
Hey.

566
00:35:23,200 --> 00:35:24,640
The door's locked properly, right?

567
00:35:25,240 --> 00:35:26,280
All set.

568
00:35:26,960 --> 00:35:28,600
- Come on, I'll help unwrap it.
- Hey.

569
00:35:29,560 --> 00:35:30,720
No, maybe not.

570
00:35:30,800 --> 00:35:32,440
I'm not used to this.

571
00:35:32,960 --> 00:35:34,280
It's too personal.

572
00:35:35,520 --> 00:35:37,800
If you're not used to it,
you have to get used to it.

573
00:35:37,880 --> 00:35:39,000
Come on.

574
00:35:40,040 --> 00:35:41,240
Ow.

575
00:35:41,320 --> 00:35:42,840
Keep it down.

576
00:35:42,920 --> 00:35:43,840
Does it hurt?

577
00:35:51,680 --> 00:35:53,080
Wow.

578
00:35:54,960 --> 00:35:56,280
Hey.

579
00:35:57,040 --> 00:35:59,000
You don't mind my foot at all?

580
00:35:59,080 --> 00:36:01,040
Foot, hand, arm, leg…

581
00:36:01,120 --> 00:36:03,040
- Ow.
- They're all body parts.

582
00:36:03,560 --> 00:36:04,760
That's a strange thing to ask.

583
00:36:05,760 --> 00:36:07,760
- Oh.
- Ouch.

584
00:36:07,840 --> 00:36:09,680
You're not really hurt.

585
00:36:11,920 --> 00:36:13,960
Scratch it for me too.
We're already this far.

586
00:36:14,040 --> 00:36:15,400
It's so itchy.

587
00:36:18,480 --> 00:36:20,400
Go on, scratch until you're satisfied.

588
00:36:20,480 --> 00:36:21,880
You won't even scratch it for me?

589
00:36:22,440 --> 00:36:24,640
I'm starting to get used to it now.
Feels kinda nice.

590
00:36:25,960 --> 00:36:28,000
Ow, that hurts.

591
00:36:28,080 --> 00:36:29,840
Stop fooling around already.

592
00:36:29,920 --> 00:36:31,960
We've wasted enough time today.

593
00:36:33,720 --> 00:36:35,560
I should apologize to you too.

594
00:36:36,200 --> 00:36:38,040
I'm not that heartless, you know.

595
00:36:39,000 --> 00:36:41,880
If Ameena really set you up to get hurt,

596
00:36:42,840 --> 00:36:44,520
I'll go after her for real.

597
00:36:45,600 --> 00:36:46,920
Thank you.

598
00:36:47,000 --> 00:36:48,600
But you don't have to do anything.

599
00:36:48,680 --> 00:36:51,840
Just let Ameena think she's won.
That's fine.

600
00:36:52,720 --> 00:36:54,120
You may not do anything, but I will.

601
00:36:54,800 --> 00:36:56,720
So she won't hurt you again.

602
00:36:56,800 --> 00:36:58,440
So you can keep working for me.

603
00:36:58,520 --> 00:37:00,480
If something happens to you, I lose out.

604
00:37:01,280 --> 00:37:03,200
- Clear?
- So,

605
00:37:03,280 --> 00:37:04,360
you're worried about yourself.

606
00:37:04,440 --> 00:37:05,720
Of course I am.

607
00:37:06,760 --> 00:37:08,040
You think I'm worried about you?

608
00:37:10,560 --> 00:37:11,880
Let's get back to business.

609
00:37:11,960 --> 00:37:15,480
Today I'll follow up on the blueprints,
the original house plans, with Mr. Arnon.

610
00:37:15,560 --> 00:37:18,560
I want to see
the original layout of this place.

611
00:37:20,080 --> 00:37:21,520
That's going to be very detailed.

612
00:37:21,600 --> 00:37:24,280
No matter how hard it is, I have to do it.

613
00:37:24,360 --> 00:37:27,200
I feel sorry for Ms. Mysterious.

614
00:37:27,800 --> 00:37:29,120
And I feel sorry for myself too.

615
00:37:29,200 --> 00:37:30,840
Oh? What about me?

616
00:37:36,440 --> 00:37:37,640
It's Mr. Arnon,

617
00:37:37,720 --> 00:37:39,280
He should've gotten the blueprints by now.

618
00:37:43,640 --> 00:37:44,800
The house registration.

619
00:37:54,840 --> 00:37:56,320
The address of this place.

620
00:38:00,320 --> 00:38:01,600
How did Arnon get this?

621
00:38:03,960 --> 00:38:05,080
Why are you wearing a cast?

622
00:38:05,600 --> 00:38:06,680
That's my business.

623
00:38:07,640 --> 00:38:10,040
Now this. This is really your business.

624
00:38:10,120 --> 00:38:11,280
The house registration
of the Vanich house.

625
00:38:11,360 --> 00:38:13,200
It's the oldest.

626
00:38:13,280 --> 00:38:15,120
It took a lot of effort to get this.

627
00:38:18,120 --> 00:38:20,040
HOUSE REGISTRATION

628
00:38:20,720 --> 00:38:21,800
Grandma Aom.

629
00:38:23,080 --> 00:38:24,320
Listed as a resident.

630
00:38:25,400 --> 00:38:26,560
Who's that?

631
00:38:26,640 --> 00:38:28,800
Judging from her date of birth,

632
00:38:29,320 --> 00:38:31,200
she must be quite old.

633
00:38:31,280 --> 00:38:33,040
Or maybe she's already passed away.

634
00:38:34,320 --> 00:38:35,200
- What?
- No.

635
00:38:35,280 --> 00:38:37,200
There's a record of relocation.

636
00:38:37,280 --> 00:38:39,040
I checked with the destination office,

637
00:38:39,800 --> 00:38:41,080
Grandma Aom is still alive.

638
00:38:41,160 --> 00:38:44,520
Is there really no way we can
just ask Grandma directly?

639
00:38:44,600 --> 00:38:46,120
Like seeing snow in Thailand.

640
00:38:46,720 --> 00:38:48,640
- Huh?
- Thick snow.

641
00:38:49,680 --> 00:38:50,480
Okay.

642
00:38:50,560 --> 00:38:52,320
Then let's go right now.

643
00:38:53,360 --> 00:38:55,320
To Grandma Aom's new house.

644
00:38:55,400 --> 00:38:58,000
We already have the address,
and Mr. Arnon checked

645
00:38:58,080 --> 00:38:58,960
that it's a real, right?

646
00:38:59,040 --> 00:39:00,360
It's in Ayutthaya.

647
00:39:00,440 --> 00:39:02,560
I thought it'd be Bangkok.

648
00:39:02,640 --> 00:39:07,040
But a round trip to Ayutthaya
won't take long. It's close.

649
00:39:07,120 --> 00:39:08,640
No way.

650
00:39:08,720 --> 00:39:10,960
You're going to drag me along
in this condition?

651
00:39:11,040 --> 00:39:12,240
I don't want to take the cast off.

652
00:39:12,320 --> 00:39:14,840
Ugh, fine. I'll drive. Okay?

653
00:39:14,920 --> 00:39:15,880
Huh?

654
00:39:20,160 --> 00:39:22,880
<i>I want Mr. Arnon to help investigate</i>

655
00:39:22,960 --> 00:39:24,480
<i>Kluay's past.</i>

656
00:39:24,560 --> 00:39:25,880
<i>Dad died</i>

657
00:39:25,960 --> 00:39:27,200
<i>because of things like this.</i>

658
00:39:27,280 --> 00:39:29,600
I don't want it to happen again.

659
00:39:29,680 --> 00:39:32,040
The day Warat gets everything
from Vanich Mall,

660
00:39:32,120 --> 00:39:34,160
that day will be ours.

661
00:39:34,240 --> 00:39:36,800
NEXT EPISODE

662
00:39:36,880 --> 00:39:38,120
Huh?

663
00:39:38,200 --> 00:39:39,800
Let's just stay out of each other's lives.

664
00:39:41,000 --> 00:39:42,200
He's my husband.

665
00:42:10,120 --> 00:42:12,280
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
